§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Given a topological space $(X, 𝒯)$, a subset $N$ of $X$ is
    called a ❬neighborhood❭ (or ❬topological neighborhood❭) of a
    point $a ∈ X$ if $N$ contains an open set that contains
    $a$. ⦉
